PrecisSetting apart, for the use and benefit of the MANTO SIPI CREE NATION, of some 1,734 hectares of land including mines and minerals situated in an unorganized territory of northern Manitoba, for the proposed Chepi Lake and Prominent Ridge Indian Reserves are approximatly 300 kilometres from the urban centre of Thompson and the proposed Hurley Island Indian Reserve is approximately 240 kilometres from the urban centre of Thompson. (LT-07-44)
